raw=Read10X_h5("filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5")
data=CreateSeuratObject(counts = raw,project="Mouse_Wnt_Tramp")
# combine online resources of mouse prostate single-cell analysis
#1. GSE146811_mmProstate10x_timecourse_rawCount.h5 is mouse prostate 10X 3' V2; DOI: 10.1126/science.aay0267
#2. GSE150692 has multiple files for different lobes anterior (AP), dorsal (DP), lateral (LP), and ventral prostate (VP) 10x 3' V2  https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.59465
# for GSE150692 GSM4556594_ML001_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt is whole prostate
# for GSE150692 GSM4556595_MM013_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt is whole prostate
# for GSE150692 GSM4556596_ML002_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt is AP
# for GSE150692 GSM4556597_ML004_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt is DP
# for GSE150692 GSM4556598_MM030_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt is VP
# for GSE150692 GSM4556599_ML005_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt is LP
# for GSE150692 GSM4556602_MM037_clean_raw_counts_matrix.txt labed as human in meta data; It is not included in this research
#3. GSE172352 has multiple files for mouse prostate, 10X 3' V2; all files were labeled as prostate tissus, no difference
# GSM5253043_muAd001_PrF_filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5
# GSM5253044_muAd002_PrF_filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5
# GSM5253045_muAd003_PrF_St_filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5
# GSM5253046_muAd007_PrFcol_GEX_filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5
#4. GSE164971 has 2 different studies, https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-022-32119-0; 10X genomic 3' V2
#4.1 GSE164969_E18-P14-P35_scRNAseq_Counts.txt contains 3 samples from E18.5_UGS, P14_prostate and P35 prostate, from their literature, they found normal NE cells
#4.2 GSE164970_hARtg-OSR1Cre_scRNAseq_Counts.txt contains both PIN and PCa cells from hARtg mouse model
